''Juilliard at Citicorp,'' a three-week series of free performances by students of the Juilliard School, begins on June 8 at 5:30 P.M. at the Citicorp Center, Lexington Avenue at 54th Street. The first performance will feature Beth Ellen Rosenbaum, a pianist; other concerts in the series, which runs through June 27, will feature duets and solo performances. The concerts will be Mondays and Saturdays at 5:30 P.M., Wednesdays at 1:30 P.M., and Fridays at 12:30 P.M. Information: 559-2330.